# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Tradevi Backend — Market Data & Broker Configuration
# Copy this file to backend/.env and fill in your API keys
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── MARKET DATA PROVIDERS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The backend uses these APIs with intelligent fallback:
# Priority for candles: Polygon (realtime) > Finnhub > YFinance (fallback, delayed)
# Priority for quotes: Finnhub (realtime) > YFinance (fallback, delayed)

# Polygon.io — HIGH QUALITY candle data (real-time or ~15-30 min delayed)
# Better than Yahoo Finance for charts and technical analysis
# Get FREE key at https://polygon.io (requires email verification)
# Set this to enable real-time candle data for better chart accuracy
POLYGON_API_KEY=your_polygon_api_key_here

# Finnhub — Real-time quotes & WebSocket price streaming
# Get FREE key at https://finnhub.io
# Set this to enable real-time price updates and WebSocket streaming
FINNHUB_API_KEY=your_finnhub_api_key_here

# ─── BROKER INTEGRATION ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Alpaca — Paper trading account (read-only portfolio data)
# Get keys from https://app.alpaca.markets
# Note: This app only reads your portfolio — it never places trades
ALPACA_API_KEY=your_alpaca_api_key_here
ALPACA_SECRET_KEY=your_alpaca_secret_key_here
ALPACA_BASE_URL=https://paper-api.alpaca.markets

# ─── OPTIONAL: TELEGRAM ALERTS ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# For trade alerts via Telegram
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=

# ─── CORS CONFIGURATION ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Allowed origins for cross-origin requests from Next.js frontend
# For development: http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
# For production: https://yourdomain.com
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000

# ─── DEPLOYMENT NOTES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# On Vercel:
# 1. Create a new Vercel KV database (redis): Settings > Storage > KV
# 2. Add these env vars to Vercel project settings:
#    - POLYGON_API_KEY
#    - FINNHUB_API_KEY
#    - ALPACA_API_KEY
#    - ALPACA_SECRET_KEY
#    - CORS_ORIGINS=https://yourdomain.vercel.app
# 3. The frontend NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL should point to your backend URL
#
# If running backend separately, ensure:
# - Backend and frontend CORS are aligned
# - Backend has valid API keys
# - Backend is accessible from frontend (check firewall, HTTPS, domain)
